This is why the EDF service starts at 3 a.m. "so that the roads are cleared when the daily migration traffic begins".
This is where it gets more difficult when the snow starts to fall at 7:30 in the morning.
This poses problems, the head of the road clearance and sandblasting service tells us "because no motorist is willing to let salty vehicles through".
Then, if it doesn't snow anymore, we take care of access roads and service roads - such as the Rat-Beil-Straße.
Side lanes and side streets come last.
Mr. Braubburger knows that this always causes some complaints.
